hatsune_diary_script.diary_text: I'm transferring to St. Theresa's Academy tomorrow!
How in the world did it come to this?\n
I'll definitely be able to have a good time there,
if I do try my very best to fit in at St. Theresa's...\n\n
almost made my poor loner heart explode...\n
the BB Brigade's leader came to my rescue!
really do connect us across all of time and space!\n
of the St. Theresa's Academy (Friendship Club) guild.
They're all so unique and full of character,
The self-introduction, bane of loners the world over!
I practiced what I'd say a thousand times,
but still managed to mess it up!
The moment I saw all my classmates' eyes looking at me,
and I think I started talking complete nonsense!\n
Everyone laughed it off in a friendly way,
but I'll never live this down...
She uses so many complicated words all the time,
sometimes I can't even understand her.
Maybe I should invest in a dictionary?\n
She's a researcher at a place called the Ivory Tower,
and she seems to stay there most of the time,
so maybe she's a loner like me!
Chloe is the same as me,
At first, I thought I might have a better chance
getting along with a fellow elf,
but I'm too scared to talk to her!\n
I could never tell her, but...\n
The total opposite of a loner like me.
I feel like I'll go blind just looking at her.\n
If I tried to have a one-on-one conversation with her,
and crumble into a million pieces.\n
If I tried to say it, I'd probably faint,
and my soul would float off to heaven...
how much Yuni helped me out today.\n
Unlike when she's being teased by Chloe and Chieru,
for the true intellectual she really is.
The way she instantly took charge,
I could see just how she became a guildmaster.
to make the whole world revere the name of the Yuni-ettes!\n\n
Was that really their guild's name?
I was always too intimidated to even try talking to her.
But now I realize she's so kind,
she even looks out for a hopeless loner like me.\n
Thanks to her help, I feel like I'm starting
to fit in with my class a bit better.\n
I heard that Chloe has lots of brothers and sisters.
it almost felt like she was a big sister to me as well!
If I learn to use this greeting too,
will I be able to become
and have lots of friends just like her?\n
I'm not ready to say it out loud,
so I'll just write it in here for today.\n
I forgot, I forgot, I forgot!\n
I have to do a presentation!
But the Mandragora I brought from the Elven Forest ran away,
and I haven't prepared a thing!\n
I can't betray Miss Misato's trust in me!\n
But really, what should I do?
should I just put together an expert's guide
on how to live without friends...?
This is all thanks to the help
the members of the Friendship Club!\n
I was suddenly surrounded by lots of people.
but I didn't run away this time!\n
Fitting in at St. Theresa's like it's the most natural thing in the world...
When he walks down the hall,
he gets some surprised looks from the other students,
but he greets them all with a smile!\n
he never falters for an instant!
Meanwhile, I can't even say a simple "Good day!"\n\n
The Mandragora I brought to school went berserk!\n
thanks to our Brigade's leader and the Friendship Club's help,
we managed to stop it before it caused too much harm.
they did it all for selfish reasons,
but I don't think that really matters.\n
I'm just so happy we were all able
at St. Theresa's Academy for Girls...
When Miss Misato first told me I'd be coming, \n
I thought it was a crazy idea.
wishing it could have lasted longer.\n
and all the classmates who were so kind to me during my academy days.\n
To everyone at St. Theresa's Academy,\n
from the bottom of my heart!
